title: Bernardeschi scores 2 goals to help Toronto beat Dallas 3-1

description: Nathaniel Lowe had four hits and two RBIs, and the Texas Rangers beat the Kansas City Royals 15-4. Lowe went 4 for 6 one night after going hitless in four at bats in Texas’ 7-1 loss on Friday.
title: Lowe has 4 hits as Rangers beat Royals 15-4

description: Kervin Arriaga and Tani Oluwaseyi scored six minutes apart in the second half and Minnesota United held on for a 2-1 victory over Atlanta United.
title: Arriaga, Oluwaseyi lead Minnesota United over Atlanta United 2-1

description: Jockey Brian Hernandez Jr. rode Mystik Dan to victory in the 150th Kentucky Derby to complete the most rewarding weekend of his career.
title: Kentucky Derby victory aboard Mystik Dan provides signature win for jockey Brian Hernandez Jr.

description: Lionel Messi set three MLS records with a goal and five assists as Inter Miami trounced the New York Red Bulls 6-2.
title: Messi has a record-setting game with a goal and 5 assists in Inter Miami's 6-2 win over Red Bulls

description: Luciano Acosta scored a goal for the third consecutive game and Roman Celentano had two saves to help FC Cincinnati beat Orlando City 1-0.
title: Luciano Acosta scores for 3rd consecutive game, Cincinnati beats Orlando City 1-0

description: Super Rugby Pacific’s playoff race changed only marginally in the weekend’s 11th round as the pacemakers showed few signs of faltering and the others jostled to keep up.
title: Status quo for the leading four teams in Super Rugby Pacific after 11 rounds

description: Logan Gilbert threw eight dominant innings, Luis Urías and Cal Raleigh homered and the Seattle Mariners beat the Houston Astros 5-0 on Saturday night.
title: Logan Gilbert throws 8 dominant innings in Mariners' 5-0 victory over Astros

description: Rodrigues gave San Jose the lead in the 5th minute and the Earthquakes never looked back in a 3-1 victory over Los Angeles FC at Levi’s Stadium.
title: Quick start sends Earthquakes to 3-1 victory over LAFC

description: Nikola Petkovic scored his first MLS goal, Enzo Copetti also scored and FC Charlotte beat the Portland Timbers 2-0.
title: Nikola Petkovic scores first MLS goal to help Charlotte beat Timbers 2-0

description: John Means pitched seven shutout innings in his season debut as the Baltimore Orioles beat the Cincinnati Reds 2-1.
title: Means tosses seven shutout innings in season debut, Orioles beat Reds 2-1

description: Anthony Edwards scored a playoff career-high 43 points, Naz Reid had 14 of his 16 points in the fourth quarter and the Minnesota Timberwolves beat the defending NBA champion Denver Nuggets 106-99 in Game 1 of the second-round series Saturday night.
title: Edwards scores 43 points, Reid erupts in 4th to help Timberwolves beat Nuggets 106-99 in Game 1

description: Dave Roberts recently joked that Shohei Ohtani should gift Roberts a Porsche when Ohtani breaks his Dodgers’ record for most home runs by a Japanese-born player.
title: Ohtani gifts Roberts a toy Porsche before breaking club mark for most HRs by a Japanese-born player

description: Ethan Champlin had 15 saves and six blocks, Merrick McHenry added 10 kills on .818 hitting with five blocks and No. 1 seed UCLA beat Long Beach State 25-20, 25-21, 27-29, 25-21 to win its second consecutive NCAA men’s volleyball championship.
title: UCLA men's volleyball beats LBSU 3-1 for 2nd straight and record 21st NCAA title

description: Tanner Banks came on after a three-hour rain delay to strike out pinch-hitter Iván Herrera in the bottom of the 10th inning, and the Chicago White Sox beat the St.
title: White Sox wait out 3-hour rain delay in 10th inning to beat Cardinals 6-5

description: Pittsburgh Pirates rookie pitcher Jared Jones is off to a dazzling start. The 22-year-old right-hander struck out 10 batters over seven near-perfect innings in a 1-0 victory over Colorado.
title: Electric Pittsburgh Pirates rookie Jared Jones is piling up strikeouts and silencing doubters

description: Bo Naylor hit his first career grand slam, Austin Hedges had his first homer since June 14 and the Cleveland Guardians beat the Los Angeles Angels 7-1.
title: Bo Naylor hits his 1st career grand slam, Guardians beat Angels 7-1

description: A person with knowledge of the injury says Dallas Mavericks center Maxi Kleber has a separated shoulder that will sideline him indefinitely.
title: Maxi Kleber of the Mavericks is out indefinitely with a separated shoulder, AP source says

description: Frank Stella, a painter, sculptor and printmaker whose constantly evolving works served as landmarks of the minimalist and post-painterly abstraction art movements, has died.
title: Frank Stella, artist renowned for blurring the lines between painting and sculpture, dies at 87

description: Taylor Pendrith has a one-shot lead going into the final round of the CJ Cup Byron Nelson. The Canadian is among several leaders seeking his first PGA Tour victory.
title: Taylor Pendrith leads Byron Nelson as one of several seeking first PGA Tour victory

description: Attorneys for a New Hampshire man who prevailed in a landmark lawsuit over abuse at a state-run youth detention center are asking for a hearing after the jury foreperson expressed dismay that the $38 million award could be slashed to $475,000.
title: Jury foreperson in New Hampshire youth center abuse trial 'devastated' that award could be slashed
